      //
      // A) Technologies required:
      //     - Web Server (example: Apache, IIS)
      //     - PHP Interpreter
      //     - XAMPP Control Panel
      //     - Visual Studio Code
      //     - Twig
      //
      // With the Web Server and PHP Interpreter, we have the capability to generate web content on the server before delivering results (HTML) back to the client. 
      // Then with the PHP interpreter, an HTTP server is able to serve dynamic pages on the fly.
      //
      //    Process required:
      //     1) The Web Server first fetches the included/required script file.
      //     2) Includes the contents in the current file.
      //     3) Then executes the merged script.
      //     4) Status change is detected.
      //     5) Attempts to start MySQL app.
      //     6) Status change is detected.
      //     7) Attempts to stop MySQL app.
      //     8) Status change is detected.
      //     9) Attempts to stop Web Server (example: Apache)
